title: arnold press
description: This is a shoulder press that involves rotating the arms from a pronated to a supinated position

title: back extension
description: This is a lower back exercise in which the body is bent at the waist, typically over a hyperextension bench, exercise ball or other equipment

title: bench press
description: This is an exercise in which the weight is pressed upwards from a lying position on a bench

title: bicep curl
description: This is an exercise in which weight is pulled using the biceps muscle in a "curling" movement of the elbow

title: burpee
description: This is a cardio exercise which requires squatting down, kicking the feet back and extending the body, bringing the feet back in, then jumping straight up

title: cable crossover
description: This is an exercise in which the arms pull on cables, in an arc, until they meet in front of the chest.

title: calf raise
description: This is an exercise in which the body is pressed up solely through movement of the ankles, thus activating the calf muscles

title: clean
description: The lifter moves a barbell from the floor to a racked position across the deltoids

title: clean and jerk
description: The clean and jerk involves first lifting a barbell from the floor to the deltoids (clean), and then raising the barbell above the head, finishing with straight arms and legs (jerk)

title: crunch
description: An exercise in which the shoulders are lifted off the ground by contracting the abdominal muscles

title: deadlift
description: This is an exercise in which weight is pulled up by extending the hips and knee

title: bench dip
description: This is an exercise in which the body is hanging and supported by both arms holding on to parallel bars or other supporting structures. The body weight is lifted by pressing on the arms.

title: front raise
description: This is a shoulder exercise in which arms are lifted in an arc in front of the body, with the elbow angle kept constant

title: high knees
description: This is a cardio exercise which requires running by bringing the knees high so that the hip makes at least a right angle

title: hip extension
description: This is an exercise in which weight is pulled by extending the hip

title: hip raise
description: This is an exercise in which the hip is raised off the ground by contracting the abdominal muscles. The legs are kept in a fixed position.

title: jm press
description: This is a triceps exercise in which weight is pressed up from the chest mainly through an extension of the elbow, thus focusing on the triceps

title: jumping jack
description: This is a cardio exercise which requires jumping between a position with arms to the side and legs together to a second position with arms straight above the head and legs wide apart

title: lateral raise
description: This is a shoulder exercise in which arms are lifted laterally in an arc, with the elbow angle kept constant

title: hamstring curl
description: This is an exercise in which weight is pulled up with the legs by "curling" the knees

title: quad extension
description: This is an exercise in which weight is pushed up by extending the knees. It is usually performed in a seated position so that only the thighs are kept in a fixed position and only the lower leg moves.

title: leg raise
description: This is an exercise in which legs are raised up from a lying position while keeping knees and rest of the body straight

title: lunge
description: This is an exercise in which weight is pressed up from a position in which one leg is in front of the body with knee bent and foot flat on the ground, and the other leg is behind the body. The body is pressed up so that both knees are straightened.

title: pike press
description: This is a shoulder-activating exercise where the body weight is pressed upwards from a V body position

title: plank
description: This is an isometric exercise in which the body weight is supported by the arms and feet, and the upper body and legs are kept straightened and rigid, facing down, in a "plank" position

title: lat pulldown
description: This is a back exercise in which weight is pulled down from above the body, usually performed by pulling down on a cable

title: pullover
description: This is a chest exercise in which the weight is pulled over the head with elbows slightly bent

title: pullup
description: This is an exercise in which the body is suspended and the weight is pulled up by pulling on a bar. The hands grip the bar in an overhand fashion (the back of the hands facing the body).

title: pushup
description: The push-up is an exercise in which the body is lifted from a prone position by pressing with the arms

title: row
description: This is a back exercise in which weights and arms are pulled back towards the body

title: russian twist
description: The Russian Twist involves a repeated twisting motion of the abdomen

title: shoulder press
description: This is an exercise in which the weight is pressed straight upwards from the shoulders

title: side skaters
description: This is an exercise in which a lateral jump is performed, landing on one foot, with the alternate leg outstretched behind.

title: situp
description: An exercise in which the entire back is lifted off the ground by contracting the abdominal muscles

title: squat
description: This is an exercise in which the body weight is pushed up with the legs from a position with knees bent at a 90 degree angle

title: step up
description: This is an exercise in which the body weight is pushed up by stepping up into a higher platform with one leg

title: thruster
description: This is an exercise which involves pressing weight up with the legs from a bent-knee position and pressing the weight up by extending the arms

title: triceps extension
description: This is an exercise in which weight is pressed overhead by extending the elbows

title: v ups
description: This is an exercise in which both the entire back and the legs are lifted off the ground simultaneously, forming a "V" with the body

title: wall sit
description: This is an isometric exercise in which knees and hips are kept at right angles with the back against a wall

title: wide grip dip
description: This is an exercise in which the body is hanging and supported by both arms holding on to parallel bars or other supporting structures. The body weight is lifted by pressing on the arms.

title: basketball
description: A sport in which two teams try to shoot a ball into the opposing team's net.

title: biking
description: Strengthen your thighs and calve muscles by going on a bike ride!

title: boxing
description: A combat sport in which two people, usually wearing protective gloves and other protective equipment such as hand wraps and mouthguards, throw punches at each other for a predetermined amount of time in a boxing ring.

title: crossfit
description: A branded fitness regimen that has gained immense popularity, with workouts based on high intensity interval training

title: dancing
description: Uplift your mood and workout your entire body by dancing!

title: hiking
description: Strengthen your legs and build your stamina by exploring nature!

title: jump rope
description: Build muscle strength and endurance by jumping rope. Try different techniques!

title: kickboxing
description: Boxing in which boxers are permitted to kick with bare feet as in karate.

title: pilates
description: An exercise regimen that is typically performed on a floor mat or with the use of specialized apparatus and aims to improve flexibility and stability by strengthening the muscles and especially the torso-stabilizing muscles of the abdomen and lower back

title: rock climbing
description: The sport or activity of climbing rock faces, especially with the aid of ropes and special equipment.

title: running
description: The runner's high is no myth; build your endurance, strength, and stamina by going on a run.

title: swimming
description: Swimming builds endurance, muscle strength, and cardiovascular fitness. helps maintain a healthy heart and lungs!

title: walking
description: Improve your overall health by taking a walk! Improve your circulation, strengthen your muscles, and support your joints.

title: yoga
description: A group of physical, mental, and spiritual practices or disciplines which originated in ancient India, including breath control, simple meditation, and the adoption of specific bodily postures, is widely practiced for health and relaxation.

title: zumba
description: An aerobic fitness program featuring movements inspired by various styles of Latin American dance and performed primarily to Latin American dance music.
